# Performance

This is the most important one.

Every feature must consider performance.

Never cause:

- unnecessary renders
- duplicate renders
- infinite renders
- stale UI
- race conditions
- duplicated requests
- memory leaks
- unnecessary state
- expensive computations
- unnecessary animations

Always:

- memoize only when beneficial
- cancel requests on unmount
- clean up listeners
- clean up timers
- clean up intervals
- clean up subscriptions
- virtualize long lists
- lazy load expensive screens
- paginate large datasets
- batch updates when possible
- avoid prop drilling
- avoid unnecessary context updates
- keep renders predictable

Never use state that can be derived.

Derived state should never be stored.

Prevent stale closures.

Prevent async state updates after unmount.

Never create new functions inside render unless necessary.

Avoid unnecessary object creation inside render.

Measure before optimizing.
